{
  "message": "test(fuzz): add 24 npy_npz_bytes corpus seeds\n\nCovers NPY/NPZ file parsing edge cases:\n\nValid NPY files:\n- 1D int64, 2D float64, 3D float32\n- Scalar int32, empty float32\n- bool, uint8, float16, complex128\n- Fortran order arrays\n\nValid NPZ files:\n- Single array, multiple arrays\n- Compressed (savez_compressed)\n- Named arrays (weights, bias)\n\nEdge cases:\n- Empty file, null bytes, all-ones bytes\n- NPY magic only, v1/v2 truncated headers\n- Invalid version (v3)\n- Minimal valid v1 header\n- ZIP magic only (for NPZ parsing)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
